          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Senior advisers to US President Trump will meet Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy at the Munich Security Conference to discuss a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-11-02-2025-br2-5-resolution-to-russian-war-in-ukraine" target="_blank">resolution to Russiaâ€™s war in Ukraine</a>. Zelenskyy is open to negotiations only if the US and Europe continue their support and provide security guarantees against Russia. Trumpâ€™s envoy, retired Lt. Gen. Keith Kellogg, prepares potential settlement options.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Zelenskyy insists any deal must prevent future Russian aggression. Russian Deputy Foreign Minister Sergei Ryabkov demands all of Vladimir Putinâ€™s conditions be met before arriving at a possible settlement. Trump has criticized Europe for not contributing enough and suggested nations repay the US for its aid. Ukraine has proposed supplying rare earth minerals to the US in exchange for financial support.</p>
